###############################################################################
Introduction to pointers in c
###############################################################################
Pointer is a variable just like other variables of c but only difference is 
unlike the other variable it stores the memory address of any other variables 
of c. This variable may be type of int, char, array, structure, function or 
any other pointers. For examples:

(1) Pointer p which is storing memory address of a int type variable:

int i=50;
int *p=&i;

(2) Pointer p which is storing memory address of an array:

int arr[20];
int (*p)[20]=&arr;

(3) Pointer p which is storing memory address of a function:

char display(void);
char(*p)(void)=&display;

(4) Pointer p which is storing memory address of struct type variable:

struct abc{
int a;
float b;
}var;
struct abc *p=&var;

